<HEAD>Top Administration Officials Called To Testify Against North</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JAMES ROWLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A host of current and former top government officials are listed as prosecution witnesses for the Iran-Contra conspiracy trial of Marine Lt. Col. <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> North </PERSON> and three co-defendants. Secretary of State <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> and two top deputies and Attorney <PERSON> Edwin </PERSON> <PERSON> Meese </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON> and two of his top aides are among the list of 105 witnesses submitted in a court filing Friday by independent counsel <PERSON> Lawrence </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Walsh </PERSON>. The list includes national security officials knowledgeable about the covert sale of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> arms to <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>, private operatives who ran the secret supply network that armed the Nicaraguan rebels, <PERSON> Contra </PERSON> leaders and wealthy donors who contributed to their cause. No date has been set for the trial of North, former national security adviser <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Poindexter </PERSON> and two arms dealers: retired <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> Maj. Gen. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> V. </PERSON> <PERSON> Secord </PERSON> and <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> Hakim </PERSON>. They are accused of conspiring to divert profits illegally from the U.S.-Iran arms sales to help the Contras during a ban on direct American military aid to the rebels. <PERSON> Walsh </PERSON> filed the witness list in advance of Monday's hearing called by <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> District Judge <PERSON> Gerhard </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gesell </PERSON> to determine if prosecutors impermissibly relied on evidence derived from the compelled congressional testimony of <LOCATION> North </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Hakim </PERSON> and <PERSON> Poindexter </PERSON>. Most of the witnesses were known to <PERSON> Walsh </PERSON>