TION> Party </ORGANIZATION> chief in March 1985. His speeches have shown him to be more conservative than <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON>. He is reported to feel glasnost has gone too far in denouncing most economic and social policies of the past. <PERSON> Ligachev </PERSON> was made a full Politburo member in April 1985, at the first <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> meeting under <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON>, without having served the customary term as a non-voting member.
