lop the market place are putting up a lot of money to take care of their problems, to relocate them,'' said <PERSON> Kihano </PERSON>. <PERSON> Won </PERSON> <PERSON> Hee </PERSON> <PERSON> You </PERSON>, who has served as a spokeswoman for the 900 vendors, said they fear the convention center will wipe out years of work to establish their businesses. The measure will allow a private developer to exceed the city's 280-foot height limit on the five-acre parcel and put up three 400-foot hotel and condominium towers In exchange for the additional height, the developer has agreed to build a 625,000 square-foot convention center facility which would be turned over to the state. Such a facility would cost the state $ 150 million to $ 200 million to build, according to <LOCATION> Cachola </LOCATION>.
