<TEXT>
 A mammogram of <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s right breast shows no sign of cancer, the White House says. While the first lady went to <LOCATION> Bethesda </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Naval </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> to have her six-month checkup following removal of her cancerous left breast, President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> had dental X-rays done there. The first couple flew by helicopter Friday to the suburban <LOCATION> Maryland </LOCATION> military facility from the <LOCATION> White </LOCATION> <LOCATION> House </LOCATION>, remained there for less than a half-hour, then went to Camp David for the weekend. `` The president and first lady completed their routine radiological procedures,'' <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> physician Dr. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Hutton </PERSON> said. `` The president had a series of routine dental X-rays in the dental clinic, while Mrs. <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> had her first post-operative mammogram,'' he said. `` The mammogram was negative. No immediate treatment of any kind is required as a result of today's procedures on the president and first lady.''
