 <ORGANIZATION> Audi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> said Friday that the suggested retail prices of 1988 <ORGANIZATION> Audi </ORGANIZATION> 5000 Series cars will rise by 3 percent on May 9. The increases will range from $ 670 for the least expensive 5000S sedan, making that model cost $ 22,850, to $ 1,060 for the most expensive 5000CS Turbo Quattro wagon, which will cost $ 36,310, the West German automaker's <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> sales and distribution arm said in a statement. Prices of 1988 <ORGANIZATION> Audi </ORGANIZATION> 80 and <ORGANIZATION> Audi </ORGANIZATION> 90 series cars will not be affected, nor will option prices or transportation charges for any models, the statement said.
