<HEAD>Oil Prices Mixed</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: For Saturday PMs</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Oil prices have closed out the week on a mixed note, as traders took profits and looked ahead to upcoming <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> talks aimed at strengthening the market. In Friday trading on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, contracts for June delivery of <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intermediate </ORGANIZATION>, the benchmark <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> crude, settled at $ 18.30 per 42-gallon barrel, down 6 cents from Thursday. Among refined products, contracts for May delivery of wholesale unleaded gasoline edged 0.16 cent lower to 52.29 cents per gallon, while wholesale heating oil closed up 0.06 cent at 50.60 cents per gallon. <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON> <PERSON> Lebow </PERSON>, senior broker and analyst at <ORGANIZATION> E.D. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> F. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Man </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, said technical trading dominated the day's activity. `` The market rallied early on follow-through optimism over the <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> meetings next week, but when it failed to get going on the upside, people just took profits,'' he said. Discussions are scheduled to begin Tuesday between representatives of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries and officials of producing countries that are not members of the 13-nation cartel. Later, the cartel will hold a full ministerial meeting. In both cases, <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> will be seeking ways of coordinating production cutbacks in order to reduce world supplies and boost prices.
